{
  "texts": [
    "The phenomenon not only undermines the reliability of the models but also raises concerns about their applicability in critical applications [3].",
    "Hallucination is attributed to various factors, including the model's reliance on patterns in the training data rather than factual understanding or real-world knowledge, and the assessors' own subjective understanding of the LLM evaluation criteria [3].",
    "Addressing this issue is crucial for advancing the utility and reliability of LLMs in producing content that is both engaging and accurate.The proposed solution to mitigate hallucination involves integrating Llama 2 7b with the Google Query API, leveraging training techniques, including transfer learning and unsupervised pre-training, which enable models to leverage vast datasets more effectively [4,5,6,7,8,9].",
    "Research has also highlighted the importance of dynamic data refreshing, where continuously updating the training corpus with recent information can help maintain the model's relevance over time [10,11,12].",
    "Moreover, incorporating external knowledge bases has been found to enhance the model's ability to generate factually accurate responses [13,14,15,16]."
  ]
}